header.gameNote: CHICAGO INVITATIONAL CHALLENGE AT HOFFMAN ESTATES IL

article.headline: Bradley 101, Rutgers 72
article.story: HOFFMAN ESTATES, Ill. (AP) -- Jeremy Crouch scored 19 points and Zach Andrews added 16 to lead Bradley to a 101-72 victory over Rutgers on Friday in the Chicago Invitational Challenge. Bradley (5-0) made quick work of Rutgers by opening the game with a 29-8 run. Will Franklin scored eight straight points for Bradley in the span. Danny Adams extended Bradley's lead to 43-16 with consecutive 3-pointers. Couch also hit consecutive 3-pointers to make it 61-27 at the half. Marquis Webb led Rutgers (1-3) with 16 points, and J.R. Inman had 14.
